23/* This file holds definitions specific to the RISCV ELF ABI. Note
24 that most of this is not actually implemented by BFD. */
25
26#ifndef _ELF_RISCV_H
27#define _ELF_RISCV_H
28
29#include "elf/reloc-macros.h"
30#include "libiberty.h"
31
32/* Relocation types. */
33START_RELOC_NUMBERS (elf_riscv_reloc_type)

38 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RISCV_RELATIVE, 3)
39 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RISCV_COPY, 4)

44 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RISCV_TLS_DTPREL64, 9)
45 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RISCV_TLS_TPREL32, 10)
46 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RISCV_TLS_TPREL64, 11)

93/* Processor specific flags for the ELF header e_flags field. */
94
95/* File may contain compressed instructions. */
96#define EF_RISCV_RVC 0x0001
97
98/* Which floating-point ABI a file uses. */
99#define EF_RISCV_FLOAT_ABI 0x0006
100
101/* File uses the soft-float ABI. */
102#define EF_RISCV_FLOAT_ABI_SOFT 0x0000
103
104/* File uses the single-float ABI. */
105#define EF_RISCV_FLOAT_ABI_SINGLE 0x0002
106
107/* File uses the double-float ABI. */
108#define EF_RISCV_FLOAT_ABI_DOUBLE 0x0004
109
110/* File uses the quad-float ABI. */
111#define EF_RISCV_FLOAT_ABI_QUAD 0x0006
112
113/* File uses the 32E base integer instruction. */
114#define EF_RISCV_RVE 0x0008
115
116/* The name of the global pointer symbol. */
117#define RISCV_GP_SYMBOL "__global_pointer$"
118
119#endif /* _ELF_RISCV_H */
